HEADWORD: Excusable
<hw>Ex*cus"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excusabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>excusable</ets>. See
<er>Excuse</er>.]</ety> <def>That may be excused, forgiven, justified,
or acquitted of blame; pardonable; <as>as, the man is
<ex>excusable</ex>; an <ex>excusable</ex> action</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Ex*cus"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Ex*cus"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>excusableness</qex> of my dissatisfaction.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excusation</ent>⟦br⟧
